{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Conditional rendering","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Learn/Framework/MarkupLanguage/Condition","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>In the frame, use <code>tt:if=\"{{condition}}\"</code> to determine if the block needs to be rendered:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>view</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\"><span class=\"token namespace\">tt:</span>if</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>{{condition}}<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>True<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>view</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>When <code>condition</code> is <code>true</code>, render <code>True</code>, if <code>false</code> no labels are rendered.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"else_block","title":"else block","isH3":false,"content":"<p>An else block can be added with <code>tt:elif</code> and <code>tt:else</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>view</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\"><span class=\"token namespace\">tt:</span>if</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>{{length &gt; 5}}<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>1<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>view</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>view</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\"><span class=\"token namespace\">tt:</span>elif</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>{{length &gt; 2}}<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>2<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>view</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>view</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\"><span class=\"token namespace\">tt:</span>else</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>3<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>view</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<blockquote>\n  <p><code>tt:elif</code> and <code>tt:else</code> must be used together with <code>tt:if</code> and must be at the same level.</p>\n</blockquote>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"multi-tab_rendering","title":"Multi-tab rendering","isH3":false,"content":"<p>By default, <code>tt:if</code> can only control one tag. If you want to control the rendering of multiple tags at the same time, you can use <code>&lt;block/&gt;</code> and <code>tt:if</code>, <code>&lt;block/&gt;</code> will not be used in actual Any tags generated in the display page.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>block</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\"><span class=\"token namespace\">tt:</span>if</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>{{true}}<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>view</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>view1<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>view</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>view</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>view2<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>view</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>block</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"hidden","title":"<code>hidden</code>","isH3":false,"content":"<p>When the result of the <code>tt:if</code> expression changes, the original node is deleted and a new node is created. If a large number of nodes cause poor performance of creation and destruction, the <code>hidden</code> property can be used to optimize it.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>view</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">hidden</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>{{condition}}<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span> True <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>view</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The <code>hidden</code> attribute does not create or destroy nodes, it is only responsible for showing and hiding nodes, so the performance of switching is higher than <code>tt:if</code>.</p>\n<blockquote>\n  <p>In general, <code>tt:if</code> has a higher switching cost and <code>hidden</code> has a higher initial rendering cost (it will render regardless of the result of the expression). Therefore, if you need to switch frequently, it is better to use <code>hidden</code>, and if you do not switch frequently, it is better to use <code>tt:if</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>","titleAsText":"hidden"}}],"toc":[{"text":"else block","id":"else_block"},{"text":"Multi-tab rendering","id":"multi-tab_rendering"},{"text":"<code>hidden</code>","id":"hidden"}],"summary":"In the frame, use tt:if=\"{{condition}}\" to determine if the block needs to be rendered:","popularity":0,"modified":null,"other_translations":[{"title":"条件渲染","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/learn/framework/markuplanguage/condition","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/en-us/learn/framework/markuplanguage/condition/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/null","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"Conditional rendering","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Learn/Framework/MarkupLanguage","title":"Markup Language"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Learn/Framework/MarkupLanguage/Condition","title":"Conditional rendering"}],"pageTitle":"Conditional rendering | MDN","noIndexing":false}}